ğŸ”¶ What is VLAN (Virtual Local Area Network)?

A VLAN is a virtual network created inside a single physical switch.
It logically separates devices into different networks even if they are connected to the same switch.

Think of it like creating multiple separate rooms inside one big hall.

ğŸ”¶ Why VLAN is Needed?

Without VLANs, all devices in a switch are in the same network, can talk to each other directly â†’ not secure and causes broadcast traffic.

VLANs help to:

âœ” Separate networks
âœ” Improve security
âœ” Reduce broadcast traffic
âœ” Segment users (Wi-Fi, Servers, CCTV, Guest network etc.)
âœ… 3. For Security & Isolation

VLANs create boundaries:
âœ” CCTV cameras â†’ VLAN 40
âœ” Biometric machines â†’ VLAN 50
âœ” IoT devices â†’ VLAN 60

These devices cannot talk to corporate network.

âœ… 4. For Voice (IP Phones)

Switch ports carry:

Data VLAN (PC traffic)

Voice VLAN (Phone traffic)

Example:

switchport access vlan 10
switchport voice vlan 200

âœ… 5. For Trunk Links Between Switches

When many VLANs need to be carried between switches â†’ use trunk ports.

Example:

Switch to core switch

Switch to Access Points

Switch to Firewall

switchport mode trunk
switchport trunk allowed vlan 10,20,30,21-25

ğŸ”¶ Types of VLANs
VLAN Type	Use
Access VLAN	For end devices (PC, Printer, CCTV)
Voice VLAN	IP phones
Management VLAN	Switch/WLC management (like VLAN 21)
Native VLAN	Used on trunk ports
Trunk VLANs	Carry multiple VLANs between switches
ğŸ”¶ Simple Example

ğŸ“Œ Without VLANs:
Everyone is in 192.168.1.0 â†’ very insecure.

ğŸ“Œ With VLANs:

HR: 192.168.10.0

Finance: 192.168.20.0

WiFi Corporate: 10.21.28.0

Guest: 10.25.10.0

Each is isolated by the switch + ACLs + firewall.

ğŸ”¶ Summary
âœ” VLAN = Logical separation inside a switch
âœ” Used to segment users, Wi-Fi, servers, cameras
âœ” Essential for security, performance, and management
âœ” Used everywhere: switches, routers, firewalls, WLCs

